<subSubSection pageId="62" pageNumber="2844" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="62.[121,761,184,412]" pageId="62" pageNumber="2844">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zheng &amp; Wittouck &amp; Salvetti &amp; Franz &amp; Harris &amp; Mattarelli &amp; O’Toole &amp; Pot &amp; Vandamme &amp; Walter &amp; Watanabe &amp; Wuyts &amp; Felis &amp; Gänzle &amp; Lebeer" authorityYear="2020" box="[121,304,263,287]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Lentilactobacillus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="62" pageNumber="2844" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[121,304,263,287]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="2844">Lentilactobacillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Len.ti.lac.to.ba.cil’lus. L. masc. adj. 
<emphasis box="[698,760,263,287]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="2844">lentus</emphasis>
slow, sluggish, referring to the slow growth of species in the genus with lactate or propanediol as carbon course; N.L. masc. n. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Beijerinck" authorityYear="1901" box="[216,353,357,381]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Lactobacillus" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="62" pageNumber="2844" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[216,353,357,381]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="2844">Lactobacillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a bacterial genus name; N.L. masc. n. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zheng &amp; Wittouck &amp; Salvetti &amp; Franz &amp; Harris &amp; Mattarelli &amp; O’Toole &amp; Pot &amp; Vandamme &amp; Walter &amp; Watanabe &amp; Wuyts &amp; Felis &amp; Gänzle &amp; Lebeer" authorityYear="2020" box="[121,304,388,412]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Lentilactobacillus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="62" pageNumber="2844" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[121,304,388,412]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="2844">Lentilactobacillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a slow [growing] lactobacillus).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="62.[120,760,434,1206]" pageId="62" pageNumber="2844">
Gram-positive, rod-shaped, catalase negative, heterofermentative. Most strains grow at 15 °C and some also grow at 45 °C, the pH range of growth is highly variable but optimal growth is typically observed below pH 6.0. The genome size ranges from 1.57 Mbp for 
<taxonomicName box="[475,759,559,583]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Lentilactobacillus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="62" pageNumber="2844" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="species" species="senioris">
<emphasis box="[475,759,559,583]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="2844">Lentilactobacillus senioris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 4.91 Mbp for 
<taxonomicName box="[320,631,590,614]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Lentilactobacillus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="62" pageNumber="2844" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="species" species="parakefiri">
<emphasis box="[320,631,590,614]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="2844">Lentilactobacillus parakefiri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the mol% G+C content of DNA ranges from 39.1–45.2 %. Strains in thegenus were isolatedfrom silage, fermented vegetables, particularly as secondary fermentation or spoilage microbiota, (spoiled) wine and cereal mashes. Generally, strains in the species lead a free-living lifestyle; individual species of the genus, particularly 
<taxonomicName box="[411,523,778,801]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Lentilactobacillus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="62" pageNumber="2844" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="species" species="senioris">
<emphasis box="[411,523,778,801]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="2844">L. senioris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, appear to transition to a specialized, host adapted lifestyle. 
<taxonomicName class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Lentilactobacillus" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="62" pageNumber="2844" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[567,760,808,832]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="2844">Lentilactobacillus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
generally metabolize a broad spectrum of pentoses, hexoses, and disaccharides. Most species metabolize lactate to 1,2-propanediol and / or 1,2-propanediol to propanol and propionate; these pathways are virtually exclusive to heterofermentative lactobacilli and, among these, most common and most frequent in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zheng &amp; Wittouck &amp; Salvetti &amp; Franz &amp; Harris &amp; Mattarelli &amp; O’Toole &amp; Pot &amp; Vandamme &amp; Walter &amp; Watanabe &amp; Wuyts &amp; Felis &amp; Gänzle &amp; Lebeer" authorityYear="2020" box="[492,685,995,1019]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Lentilactobacillus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="62" pageNumber="2844" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[492,685,995,1019]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="2844">Lentilactobacillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Most 
<taxonomicName box="[121,394,1027,1051]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Lentilactobacillus" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="62" pageNumber="2844" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[121,310,1027,1051]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="2844">Lentilactobacillus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
also convert agmatine, a product of bacterial decarboxylation of arginine, via the agmatine deiminase pathway [
<bibRefCitation author="Zheng J &amp; Ruan L &amp; Sun M &amp; Ganzle M." box="[348,378,1089,1113]" journalOrPublisher="Appl Environ Microbiol" pageId="62" pageNumber="2844" pagination="7233 - 7243" part="81" refId="ref60098" refString="14. Zheng J, Ruan L, Sun M, Ganzle M. A genomic view of lactobacilli and pediococci demonstrates that phylogeny matches ecology and physiology. Appl Environ Microbiol 2015; 81: 7233 - 7243." title="A genomic view of lactobacilli and pediococci demonstrates that phylogeny matches ecology and physiology" type="journal article" year="2015">14</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Arena ME &amp; Landete JM &amp; Manca de Nadra MC &amp; Pardo I &amp; Ferrer S." box="[391,435,1089,1113]" pageId="62" pageNumber="2844" pagination="158 - 165" refId="ref73904" refString="326. Arena ME, Landete JM, Manca de Nadra MC, Pardo I, Ferrer S. Factors affecting the production of putrescine from agmatine by Lactobacillus hilgardii xB isolated from wine. J Appl Microbiol 2008; 105: 158 - 165." type="journal article" year="2008">326</bibRefCitation>
]; in lactobacilli, this pathway is associated with a free-living lifestyle. 
<taxonomicName class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Lentilactobacillus" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="62" pageNumber="2844" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[570,760,1120,1144]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="2844">Lentilactobacillus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
are used commercially as silage starter cultures, and in few dairy and cereal applications.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="62" pageNumber="2844" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="62.[121,760,1229,1315]" pageId="62" pageNumber="2844">
Aphylogenetic tree on the basis of 16S rRNA genes of all species in the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zheng &amp; Wittouck &amp; Salvetti &amp; Franz &amp; Harris &amp; Mattarelli &amp; O’Toole &amp; Pot &amp; Vandamme &amp; Walter &amp; Watanabe &amp; Wuyts &amp; Felis &amp; Gänzle &amp; Lebeer" authorityYear="2020" box="[345,528,1260,1284]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Lentilactobacillus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="62" pageNumber="2844" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[345,528,1260,1284]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="2844">Lentilactobacillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is provided in 
<figureCitation captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[185,216,1617,1636]" captionTargetBox="[264,1323,181,1565]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[264,1323,181,1565]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 6. Gene family presence/absence patterns in Lactobacillaceae and Leuconostocaceae. Each column represents a gene family presence/absence pattern in species of Lactobacillaceae and Leuconostoaceae, where presence is indicated with a dot. The absolute number of gene families that conform to each pattern is visualized in the marginal bar plot at the top. Separations between phylogroups are indicated with horizontal black lines. We defined genes that were present in all genomes of a clade and in none of the genomes outside of that clade as ‘signature genes’ (dark blue); other genes are shown in light blue. Only presence/absence patterns followed by four or more gene families are shown. Patterns of presence in a single species or all species are not shown. Unassigned species are clusters of closely related genomes which could not be assigned to a known species due to low whole-genome similarity to a type strain and/or low 16S rRNA similarity to a type strain." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4730552" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4730552/files/figure.png" pageId="62" pageNumber="2844">Figure S6S</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="62.[121,760,1337,1424]" pageId="62" pageNumber="2844">
The type speciesof the genus is 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zheng &amp; Wittouck &amp; Salvetti &amp; Franz &amp; Harris &amp; Mattarelli &amp; O’Toole &amp; Pot &amp; Vandamme &amp; Walter &amp; Watanabe &amp; Wuyts &amp; Felis &amp; Gänzle &amp; Lebeer" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Zheng &amp; Wittouck &amp; Salvetti &amp; Franz &amp; Harris &amp; Mattarelli &amp; O’Toole &amp; Pot &amp; Vandamme &amp; Walter &amp; Watanabe &amp; Wuyts &amp; Felis &amp; Gänzle &amp; Lebeer" baseAuthorityYear="2020" box="[474,760,1337,1361]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Lentilactobacillus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="62" pageNumber="2844" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="species" species="buchneri" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[474,760,1337,1361]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="2844">Lentilactobacillus buchneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[121,242,1369,1393]" pageId="62" pageNumber="2844" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
; 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zheng &amp; Wittouck &amp; Salvetti &amp; Franz &amp; Harris &amp; Mattarelli &amp; O’Toole &amp; Pot &amp; Vandamme &amp; Walter &amp; Watanabe &amp; Wuyts &amp; Felis &amp; Gänzle &amp; Lebeer" authorityYear="2020" box="[254,439,1369,1393]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Lentilactobacillus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="62" pageNumber="2844" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[254,439,1369,1393]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="2844">Lentilactobacillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was previously referred to as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zheng &amp; Wittouck &amp; Salvetti &amp; Franz &amp; Harris &amp; Mattarelli &amp; O’Toole &amp; Pot &amp; Vandamme &amp; Walter &amp; Watanabe &amp; Wuyts &amp; Felis &amp; Gänzle &amp; Lebeer" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Zheng &amp; Wittouck &amp; Salvetti &amp; Franz &amp; Harris &amp; Mattarelli &amp; O’Toole &amp; Pot &amp; Vandamme &amp; Walter &amp; Watanabe &amp; Wuyts &amp; Felis &amp; Gänzle &amp; Lebeer" baseAuthorityYear="2020" box="[123,241,1400,1424]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Lentilactobacillus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="62" pageNumber="2844" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="species" species="buchneri">
<emphasis box="[123,241,1400,1424]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="2844">L. buchneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group.
</paragraph>
